        <Summary>It's a free, cross-platform and open-license GUI Toolkit</Summary>
        <Description>It provides low-level core widgets, advanced composite widgets, and high-level visualization-oriented widgets that can be interfaced to visualization libraries like VTK. KWWidgets is an object-oriented C++ toolkit that can interact and co-exist with Tcl/Tk directly from C++. It is wrapped automatically into a Tcl package, and therefore can be used directly from Tcl/Tk also, allowing for fast-prototyping and scripting.</Description>
